    "topic": "History of the Indian Space Program",
    "subtopics": [
      {
        "subtopic": "Timeline",
        "content": "• 1962 – INCOSPAR formed under Dr. Vikram Sarabhai.\n• 1969 – Establishment of ISRO.\n• 1972 – Incorporated into Department of Space (DOS).\n• 1975 – India’s first satellite Aryabhata launched.\n• 1980s–90s – Development of INSAT, IRS, and PSLV systems.\n• 2008 – Chandrayaan-1 (Moon mission).\n• 2013 – Mangalyaan (Mars Orbiter Mission).\n• 2020s – Gaganyaan (Human spaceflight program) in progress."
